title: Stevie Ray Vaughan Discography (@256kbps)
description:
Most likely the most comprehensive collection of SRV you will find. it includes:

Stevie Ray Vaughan and Double Trouble:
-Texas Flood 1983
-Couldn't Stand the Weather 1984
-Soul to Soul 1985
-In Step
-Live Alive 1986
-Live at Carnegie Hall
-Live at the El Mocambo
-Live at Pier 84, NYC
-Live in Austin TX
-Live at Montreux (two shows, '82 and '85)
-Live at Harling's Upstairs 
-In the Beginning (4.1.1980, Double Trouble's 3rd or 4th show)
-The Last Show, Alpine Valley, Wisconsin, 8.26.1990 the day SRV passed (2 discs)

Stevie Ray Vaughan Solo and with other bands:

with the band before double trouble, not sure of their name:
-Accolades

-Bluebird Lounge

with the Blackbirds:
-The Blackbirds 1973 live at some party/bar in austin, tx

with Albert King's band:
-In Session

Vaughan Brothers:
-Family Style

with Dick Dale:
-Pipeline (one track)

with David Bowie:
-Let's Dance (one track SRV jams on on Bowie's 1983 album of the same name)

-Rehearsal tape with SRV 4-23-1983 2 discs (yeah, SRV almost toured with Bowie, but decided not too. most of the tracks on this don't display his prowess on the guitar, but these ones definitely do: Fame, Let's Dance, TVC-15, Stay. Another funny thing on this, the background singers fuck up once in a while, and I swear somehow you can HEAR Bowie's glare at them.....anyway. extremely rare, this one.

-Unplugged and Jammin' (an album crammed with various rarities, his MTV unplugged,  and duets with other

Enjoy!

RIP S.R.V. Hopefully he's jammin' with Hendrix in heaven. or wherever.....

SHARING IS CARING. BE LIKE JOHNNY APPLESEED.	

AGAIN I'M REALLY SORRY TO EVERYONE THAT'S BEEN DOWNLOADING THIS THAT GOT STUCK AT 99.1
